{"parse":{"title":"onion","pageid":37006,"redirects":[],"wikitext":"{{also|.onion|Onion}}\n==English==\n{{wp}}\n[[File:Field with onions.jpg|thumb|onions ({{senseno|en|Q20875685}}) growing in a farm field]]\n[[File:Onions.jpg|thumb|onions ({{senseno|en|Q3406628}}) ready for the kitchen]]\n[[File:Allium cepa - 2 (2002). (32335962167).jpg|thumb|a sliced onion]]\n[[File:Allium cepa 15-p.bot-lilia.alliu-008.jpg|thumb|onions in scallion form]]\n[[File:Allium cepa champ de semences Tusson.jpg|thumb|onion crop in flower]]\n[[File:Kluse - Allium cepa - Zwiebel 03 ies.jpg|thumb|flowering onion, with a bee]]\n\n===Alternative forms===\n* {{alter|en|onyon||obsolete}}\n\n===Etymology===\nFrom {{inh|en|enm|onyoun}}, {{m|enm|oynoun}}, from {{der|en|fro|oignon}}, from {{der|en|la|ūniōnem}}, accusative of {{m|la|unio#Etymology 3|ūniō|t=onion}}, which had also been borrowed into Old English as {{m|ang|yne}}, {{m|ang|ynnelēac|t=onion}} (> {{cog|enm|hynne-leac}}, {{m|enm|henne-leac}}). Displaced the inherited term {{m|en|ramsons}}.\n* {{sense|soy}} Stems from a {{w|4chan}} [[wordfilter|word filter]] which changes the word {{m|en|soy}} to ''onions''. The word filter was implemented in relation to the \"alpha onion eater\" [[meme]], which is depicted as the direct opposite of the [[soy boy]].\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|en|/ˈʌn.jən/|a=RP,GA}}\n** {{audio|en|En-uk-onion.ogg|a=London}}\n** {{audio|en|en-us-onion.ogg|a=California}}\n* {{IPA|en|/ˈʌn.jɪn/|qual2=nonstandard|/ˈʌŋ.jɪn/|a=Canada}}\n* {{IPA|en|/ˈɐn.jən/|qual2=nonstandard|/ˈɐŋ.jən/|a=Australia,NZ}}\n* {{IPA|en|/ˈɔnɪjən/|a=Indic}}\n* {{i|dialectal|obsolete}} {{IPA|en|/ˈɪŋ.ən/|/ˈɪn.jən/}}<ref>{{R:Bingham IP|75}}</ref><ref>{{R:en:Hurd:1847|Onion|3|86}}</ref><ref>{{R:Stanley SET|I|12|27}}</ref>\n* {{rhymes|en|ʌnjən|s=2}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{en-noun}}\n\n# {{senseid|en|Q20875685}} A [[monocotyledonous]] plant ({{taxfmt|Allium cepa|species}}), allied to [[garlic]], used as vegetable and spice.\n#: {{cot|en|wild onion|spring onion<id:Q27938><qq:Welsh onion sense>}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|year=1944 |title=Circular of Information - Issues 323-395  |author=Oregon. Agricultural experiment station |page=3 |ISBN= |passage=Some of the weeds that cause an undesirable flavor in milk are: '''onion''', tarweed, scaleweed, garlic, mustard, pepper grass. }}\n#* {{quote-text|en|year=2021|author=Rose Ray; Caro Langton|title=Into Green: Everyday Ways to Find and Lose Yourself in Nature|page=62\n|passage=To get started, how about creating an edible window box? Sowed in the spring, salad seeds like radish, lettuce and spring '''onion''' will germinate so quickly that you'll be harvesting a crop in a month or two.}}\n# {{senseid|en|Q3406628}} The [[bulb]] of such a plant.\n#: {{ux|en|My eyes are stinging from the chopped '''onions'''.}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|year=1961|author={{w|Harry E. Wedeck}}|title=Dictionary of Aphrodisiacs|publisher=The Citadel Press|location=New York|page=158|passage=Among the ancient Greeks, '''onions''' are most frequently mentioned as a stimulus to sexual desire.}}\n#* '''1962''' (quoting '''1381''' text), {{w|Hans Kurath}} & Sherman M. Kuhn, eds., ''{{w|Middle English Dictionary}}'', Ann Arbor, Mich.: {{w|University of Michigan Press}}, [[Special:BookSources/978-0-472-01044-8|ISBN 978-0-472-01044-8]], page 1242:\n#*: '''dorrẹ&#773;''', '''dōrī''' adj. & n. {{...}} <u>cook</u>. glazed with a yellow substance; pome(s ~, sopes ~. {{...}} 1381 <u>Pegge Cook. Recipes</u> p. 114: For to make Soupys dorry. Nym '''onyons''' {{...}} Nym wyn {{...}} toste wyte bred and do yt in dischis, and god Almande mylk.\n#* {{quote-journal|en|date=2015-09-04|author=|title=In Minnesota’s Iron Range, Midwestern With a Modern Twist|work=w:The New York Times|url=http://www.nytimes.com/2015/09/06/travel/mr-roberts-resort-review.html\n|passage=Goulash, a local favorite, was brought up-to-date with seared grass-fed rib-eye, stewed cippolini '''onions''' and roasted cherry tomatoes.}}\n# {{senseid|en|Q20875685 and any of various similar plants}} Any of various plants, mostly of the genus {{taxfmt|Allium|genus}}, that are [[more or less]] similar to {{taxfmt|Allium cepa|species}}.\n#: {{hypo|en|spring onion|wild onion}}\n#: {{ux|en|Many '''onions''' are delicious; domesticated '''onions''' such as ''Allium cepa'' and ''Allium fistulosum'' are especially good, but even wild '''onions''' such as ''Allium canadense'' and ''Allium validum'' are nice in small doses.}}\n# {{lb|en|slang}} Of a [[drug]], an [[ounce]].\n# {{lb|en|obsolete|_|baseball|_|slang}} A [[ball]].\n# {{lb|en|obsolete|slang}} A [[watch-seal]].\n#* {{quote-book|en|year=1846|author=George William MacArthur Reynolds|title=The Mysteries of London|page=60|text={{...}} M was a Magsman, frequenting Pall-Mall; / N was a Nose that turned chirp on his pal; / O was an '''Onion''', possessed by a swell; / P was a Pannie, done niblike and well. {{...}}}}\n# {{alt case|en|Onion||an inhabitant of Bermuda; a Bermudian}}.\n# {{lb|en|4chan|slang}} [[soy|Soy]], {{n-g|particularly when used in compound words related to the [[soy boy]] stereotype}}.\n\n====Synonyms====\n* {{sense|vegetable}} {{l|en|violet}} {{q|UK dialect}}\n\n====Derived terms====\n{{col|en\n|{{vern|Altai onion}} ({{taxlink|Allium altaicum|species}})|{{vern|angled onion}} ({{taxlink|Allium triquetrum|species}})|{{vern|autumn onion}} ({{taxfmt|Allium stellatum|species}})\n|{{vern|baby onion}} ({{taxlink|Allium porrum var. sectivum|variety}})|[[ball-head onion]] ({{taxlink|Allium sphaerocephalum|species}})|{{vern|Bangalore rose onion}}|Bermuda onion|blooming onion|{{vern|bog onion}} ({{taxfmt|Arisaema triphyllum|species}}, {{taxlink|Owenia cepiodora|species}})|[[Bristol onion]] ({{taxlink|Allium sphaerocephalon|species}})|[[brown onion]] ({{taxlink|Allium moly|species}})|bucky onion,buckyonion|{{vern|bulb onion}} ({{taxfmt|Allium cepa|species}})|bulge in the onion bag,bulge the onion bag|{{vern|bunching onion}} ({{taxfmt|Allium fistulosum|species}})|{{vern|button onion}} ({{taxlink|Allium × proliferum|nothospecies}})\n|[[Canada onion]] ({{taxlink|Allium canadense|species}})|{{vern|Cape poison onion}} ({{taxlink|Ornithoglossum glaucum|species}})|{{vern|Catawissa onion}} ({{taxlink|Allium × proliferum|nothospecies}})|[[Chinese onion]] ({{taxfmt|Allium chinense|species}})|cipolline onion|{{vern|climbing onion}} ({{taxlink|Bowiea volubilis|species}})|{{vern|coast flatleaf onion}} ({{taxlink|Allium falcifolium|species}})|cocktail onion|{{vern|common onion}} ({{taxfmt|Allium cepa|species}})|{{vern|crow onion}} ({{taxfmt|Allium vineale|species}})\n|[[desert onion]] ({{taxfmt|Allium macropetalum|species}})|{{vern|dry onion}} ({{taxfmt|Allium cepa|species}})\n|eat the onion|{{vern|Egyptian onion}} ({{taxlink|Allium × proliferum|nothospecies}})\n|flaming onion|{{vern|flowering onion}} ({{taxlink|Allium neopolitanum|species}})|French onion soup\n|garlion|{{vern|giant onion}} ({{taxlink|Allium giganteum|species}})|glass onion|[[green onion]] ({{taxfmt|Allium fistulosum|species}})|{{vern|gypsy onion}} ({{taxfmt|Allium ursinum|species}})\n|{{vern|Hooker's onion}} ({{taxfmt|Allium acuminatum|species}}\n|is someone cutting onions|onion volcano\n|[[Japanese bunching onion]] ({{taxfmt|Allium fistulosum|species}})|{{vern|jeweled onion}} ({{taxlink|Allium serra|species}})\n|[[know one's onions]]\n|{{vern|long green onion}} ({{taxfmt|Allium fistulosum|species}})|{{vern|long onion}}|{{vern|long-root onion}} ({{taxlink|Allium victorialis|species}})|{{vern|long-stamen onion}} ({{taxlink|Allium macrostemon|species}})\n|[[Maori onion]] ({{taxlink|Bulbinella|genus}} spp.)|[[multiplier onion]] ({{taxfmt|Allium cepa var. aggregatum|variety}})\n|{{vern|Naples onion}} ({{taxlink|Allium neapolitanum|species}})|[[nodding onion]] ({{taxfmt|Allium cernuum|species}})\n|off one's onion|{{vern|one-leaf onion}} ({{taxlink|Allium unifolium|species}})\n|{{vern|onion asphodel}} ({{taxlink|Asphodelus fistulosus|species}})\n|onion bag|{{vern|onion bamboo}} ({{taxlink|Pseudosasa japonica var. tsutsumiana|variety}})|onion booty|onion bottle|onion bread\n|[[onion couch]] ({{taxlink|Arrhenatherum elatius|species}})\n|onion dome|{{vern|onion downy mildew}} ({{taxlink|Peronospora destructor|species}})\n|onioned|{{vern|onion eelworm}} ({{taxlink|Ditylenchus dipsaci|species}})\n|onion fish|onion flute|[[onion fly]] ({{taxlink|Delia antiqua|species}})\n|[[onion grass]], [[oniongrass]] ({{taxfmt|Allium vineale|species}}, {{taxfmt|Melica|genus}} spp., {{taxfmt|Romulea|genus}} spp.))\n|onionin A|onionized\n|onion Johnny\n|Onionland|{{vern|onion-leafed asphodel}} ({{taxlink|Asphodelus fistulosus|species}})|onionless|onionlike|{{vern|onion louse}} ({{taxlink|Thrips tabaci|species}})\n|[[onion maggot]] ({{taxlink|Delia antiqua|species}})|{{vern|onion mildew}}\n|onion network\n|onion paper|{{vern|onion powdery mildew}} ({{taxlink|Leveillula taurica|species}})\n|onion red|onion ring|onion roll|{{vern|onion root twitch}} ({{taxlink|Arrhenatherum elatius|species}})|onion router|onion routing\n|{{vern|onion scab}} ({{taxlink|Colletotrichum circinans|species}})|[[onion seed]] ({{taxfmt|Nigella sativa|species}})|onion service|onion skin,onionskin|onion skinning|onion-skinned|[[onion smudge]] ({{taxlink|Colletotrichum circinans|species}})|[[onion smut]] ({{taxlink|Urocystis cepulae|species}})|onion snow|onion squash|{{vern|onion stick}}|onion straw\n|[[onion thrips]] ({{taxlink|Thrips tabaci|species}})|{{vern|onion twitch}} ({{taxlink|Arrhenatherum elatius|species}})\n|oniontini|onion peel\n|[[onionweed]], {{vern|onion weed}} ({{taxlink|Allium neapolitanum|species}}, {{taxlink|Asphodelus fistulosus|species}})|[[onionwood]] ({{taxlink|Dysoxylum mollissimum subsp. molle|subspecies}})\n|oniony|{{taxlink|Onion yellow dwarf virus|species}}\n|{{vern|oriental onion}} ({{taxfmt|Allium chinense|species}})\n|{{vern|Pacific onion}}, {{vern|Pacific mountain onion}} ({{taxlink|Allium validum|species}})|[[pearl onion]] ({{taxlink|Allium porrum var. sectivum|variety}})|peel back the onion|peel the onion|{{vern|perennial onion}} ({{taxlink|Allium × cornutum|nothospecies}})|{{vern|pom-pom onion}} ({{taxlink|Allium serra|species}})|[[potato onion]] ({{taxfmt|Allium cepa var. aggregatum|variety}})|{{vern|prairie onion}} ({{taxfmt|Allium stellatum|species}})|{{vern|purple onion}}\n|quantum onion\n|red onion|{{vern|red-skinned onion}}, [[redskin onion]] ({{taxlink|Allium haematochiton|species}})\n|[[salad onion]] ({{taxfmt|Allium fistulosum|species}})|{{vern|serrated onion}} ({{taxlink|Allium serra|species}})|{{vern|scytheleaf onion}} ({{taxlink|Allium falcifolium|species}})|[[sea onion]] ({{taxlink|Urginea maritima|species}})|{{vern|shore onion}} ({{taxfmt|Allium schoenoprasum|species}})|{{vern|Siberian onion}}|[[silverskin onion]] ({{taxlink|Allium ampeloprasum var. sectivum|variety}})|[[Spanish onion]] ({{taxlink|Allium cepa var. cepa|variety}})|[[spring onion]] ({{taxfmt|Allium fistulosum|species}})|spunion\n|{{vern|swamp onion}} ({{taxlink|Allium validum|species}})|{{vern|sweet onion}}\n|{{vern|table onion}} ({{taxfmt|Allium cepa|species}})|take out an onion|{{vern|tapertip onion}} ({{taxfmt|Allium acuminatum|species}})|{{vern|top onion}}, {{vern|topset onion}} ({{taxlink|Allium × proliferum|nothospecies}})|[[tree onion]] ({{taxlink|Allium × proliferum|nothospecies}}, syn. {{taxlink|Allium cepa var. viviparum|variety}})|{{vern|triploid onion}} ({{taxlink|Allium × cornutum|nothospecies}})|{{vern|Turkestan onion}} ({{taxlink|Allium karataviense|species}})|[[twincrest onion]] ({{taxfmt|Allium bisceptrum|species}})\n|{{vern|Vidalia onion}}\n|{{vern|Wakegi onion}}, [[walking onion]] ({{taxlink|Allium × proliferum|nothospecies}})|[[Welsh onion]] ({{taxfmt|Allium fistulosum|species}})|{{vern|white onion}}|[[wild onion]] ({{taxfmt|Allium|genus}} spp., {{taxlink|Asphodelus fistulosum|species}}, {{taxlink|Dipcadi glaucum|species}})|{{vern|winter onion}} ({{taxfmt|Allium fistulosum|species}})\n|{{vern|yard onion}} ({{taxfmt|Allium cepa|species}})|[[yellow onion]] ({{taxlink|Allium moly|species}})\n}}\n\n====Descendants====\n* {{desc|bi|anian}}\n* {{desc|tpi|anian}}\n* {{desc|mi|aniana|bor=1}}\n\n====Translations====\n{{trans-top|''Allium cepa''}}{{multitrans|data=\n* Abkhaz: {{tt|ab|ахыц}}\n* Afar: {{tt|aa|basáltu}}\n* Afrikaans: {{tt+|af|ui}}\n* Aiton: {{t-needed|aio}}\n* Alabama: {{tt|akz|kasooma}}\n* Albanian: {{tt+|sq|qepë|f}} {{t|sq|Kep}}(gheg)\n* Altai:\n*: Southern Altai: {{tt|alt|согоно}}, {{tt|alt|согонок}}\n* Amharic: {{tt|am|ሽንኩርት}}\n* Amis: {{t|ami|sowana}}\n* Ankave: {{tt|aak|anianɨ'}}\n* Arabic: {{tt|ar|بَصَل|m}}\n*: Chadian Arabic: {{t|shu|بصل|m|tr=basal}} {{qualifier|collective}}, {{t|shu|بصلاي|f|tr=basalāy}} {{qualifier|singulative}}\n*: Egyptian Arabic: {{tt|arz|بصل|m|tr=baṣal}} {{qualifier|collective}}, {{tt|arz|بصلة|f|tr=baṣala}} (''[[singulative]]'')\n*: Gulf Arabic: {{tt|afb|بُصَل|m|tr=bʊṣəl}}\n*: Moroccan Arabic: {{tt|ary|بصل|m|tr=bṣal}} {{qualifier|collective}}, {{tt|ary|بصلة|f|tr=baṣla}} (''[[singulative]]'')\n* Aramaic: {{tt|arc|בָּצְלָא}}\n*: Assyrian Neo-Aramaic: {{tt|aii|ܒܸܨܠܵܐ|tr=biṣla|m}}\n*: Classical Syriac: {{tt|syc|ܒܨܠܐ|tr=beṣlā}}\n* Armenian: {{tt+|hy|սոխ}}\n* Aromanian: {{tt|rup|tseapã|f}}\n* Assamese: {{tt|as|পিয়াঁজ}}, {{tt|as|পনৰু}}\n* Asturian: {{tt+|ast|cebolla|f}}\n* Atayal: {{tt|tay|negi'}}\n* Avar: {{tt|av|пер}}\n* Azerbaijani: {{tt+|az|soğan}}\n* Bangi: {{t|bni|litungulu}}\n* Bashkir: {{tt|ba|һуған}}\n* Basque: {{tt|eu|tipula}}\n* Belarusian: {{tt|be|цыбу́ля|f}}, {{tt|be|лук|m}} {{q|regional}}\n* Bengali: {{tt+|bn|পেঁয়াজ}}\n* Bezhta: {{tt|kap|хагъо}}\n* Bhojpuri: {{tt|bho|𑂣𑂱𑂄𑂔}}\n* Bikol:\n*: Central Bikol: {{tt+|bcl|sibulyas}}\n* Breton: {{tt+|br|ognonenn|m}}\n* Bulgarian: {{tt+|bg|лук|m}}\n* Burmese: {{tt+|my|ကြက်သွန်နီ}}, {{tt+|my|ကြက်သွန်}}\n* Buryat: {{tt|bua|һонгино}}\n* Catalan: {{tt+|ca|ceba|f}}\n* Cebuano: {{tt|ceb|sibuyas}}\n* Chakma: {{t-needed|ccp}}\n* Chamicuro: {{tt|ccc|sewoyo}}\n* Chavacano: {{t|cbk|cebollas}}\n* Chechen: {{tt|ce|хох}}\n* Chichewa: {